      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys 2022 R2 used under FDA-recognized QMS; version control and audit trail documented per ISO 9001. Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) operate under documented quality management systems with version-controlled input decks and reproducible run scripts. Independent re-execution by a second analyst confirmed identical QoI outputs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/numerical-code-verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification against ASME V&V 10 benchmark problems; patch test passed for hexahedral and tetrahedral element libraries.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical element library verified against published NAFEMS benchmarks. Patch test and single-element tests confirm correct implementation of contact and large-deformation kinematics relevant to the F1717 loading scenario."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/discretization-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Global Richardson extrapolation GCI < 2% for all three QoIs; mesh convergence study with at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities (coarse ~120k, medium ~480k, fine ~1.9M elements) applied to the screw-rod-block assembly. GCI for stiffness: 0.8%; yield force: 1.1%; force at 40 mm: 1.4%. All within the 2% threshold."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/numerical-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residual norms below 1e-6 at every load step; arc-length method used for post-yield path following.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used for pre-yield regime; arc-length continuation applied beyond yield. Force residual norms confirmed below 1e-6 at all 250 load increments. No divergence events recorded."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation protocol reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition application and material assignment verified against engineering drawings.",
      "rationale": "A second FDA analyst independently reconstructed boundary conditions from the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and confirmed agreement with the primary analyst's setup. Material assignments cross-checked against certified material test reports."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening selected; justification documented against known failure modes of Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screws under bending.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as bilinear isotropic hardening continuum. Thread geometry explicitly meshed; polyethylene block modeled as hyperelastic (Mooney-Rivlin, 2-term). Model form consistent with published literature on F1717 FEA (Nagaraja 2022, Goel 2006)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws; uncertainty in inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000).",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.8 GPa) for Ti-6Al-4V sourced from lot-specific tensile test coupons. CMM-measured screw geometry used for CAD reconstruction. Monte Carlo propagation shows QoI sensitivity dominated by yield strength (CV 3.2%)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 production screws from at least two manufacturing lots; dimensional inspection confirms geometric conformance to drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws drawn from two production lots (Lot A: n=6, Lab 1; Lot B: n=5, Lab 2). All screws within drawing tolerances per CMM report. Inter-lot variability in stiffness: CV 4.1%."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two displacement rates and two temperature conditions to characterize rate and thermal sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min) and ambient temperature only, consistent with ASTM F1717 but insufficient to characterize rate or thermal dependence. This factor is below the required level; the gap is acknowledged and accepted given the quasi-static, non-thermal COU scope.",
      "gapJustification": "Single test condition accepted because the COU is limited to quasi-static room-temperature loading; rate and temperature effects are outside the intended use scope for this submission."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/equivalency-of-input-parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to experimental specimen properties measured post-test; friction coefficients calibrated from independent coupon tests.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 FEA runs used specimen-specific CMM geometry and lot-specific material properties. Contact friction coefficient (μ=0.22) calibrated from independent Ti-6Al-4V/UHMWPE coupon friction tests. Input equivalency confirmed by traceability matrix."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval metric computed per ASME V&V 40 Eq. 5-1; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (0.84), yield force (0.61), and force at 40 mm (1.71). All three values below 1.96. Systematic bias (FEA consistently 3–9% above experimental mean) noted and attributed to idealized thread geometry in CAD reconstruction."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-of-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly map to the clinical failure modes identified in the risk analysis: screw fatigue and construct loosening.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness governs load sharing with posterior column; yield force is the onset of permanent deformation linked to fatigue crack initiation; force at 40 mm represents gross structural failure. All three QoIs are directly referenced in the device risk file."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-of-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
